## Domains

Domains represent logical groupings of business functions, data, or ownership. They define boundaries for governance, cost allocation, and data stewardship.

| Domain Abbreviation | Description |
|---------------------|-------------|
{%- for domain in domain_list %}
| `{{ domain | upper }}` | |
{%- endfor %}

{%- if account_strategy == "Single Account" %}
**Usage:** Domains will appear at the **database level** in object names.
{%- elif account_strategy == "Multi-Account (Environment-based)" %}
**Usage:** Domains will appear at the **database level** within each environment account.
{%- elif account_strategy == "Multi-Account (Domain-based)" %}
**Usage:** Domains will appear at the **account level**.
{%- elif account_strategy == "Multi-Account (Domain + Environment)" %}
**Usage:** Domains will appear at the **account level** combined with environments.
{%- endif %}

## Environments

Environments represent stages in the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC), used to isolate data and application development based on maturity and stability.

| Environment Abbreviation | Stage | Description |
|--------------------------|-------|-------------|
{%- for env in environment_list %}
| `{{ env | upper }}` | | |
{%- endfor %}

{%- if account_strategy == "Single Account" %}
**Usage:** Environments will appear at the **database level** in object names.
{%- elif account_strategy == "Multi-Account (Environment-based)" %}
**Usage:** Environments will appear at the **account level**.
{%- elif account_strategy == "Multi-Account (Domain-based)" %}
**Usage:** Environments will appear at the **database level** within each domain account.
{%- elif account_strategy == "Multi-Account (Domain + Environment)" %}
**Usage:** Environments will appear at the **account level** combined with domains.
{%- endif %}

